The paper discusses a new sparsity model for fusion frames and its application in compressed sensing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of information processing, including signal processing and coding theory. The paper also involves signal processing techniques, which makes cs.SP (Signal Processing) another likely sub-category. The use of convex optimization and probabilistic analysis suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MM (Multimedia), which deal with optimization and statistical modeling. Finally, the paper involves numerical simulations and sampling conditions, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
